INSTALL
  0-
    from git (last version)
      mkdir -p ~/.gnome2/rhythmbox/plugins
      cd ~/.gnome2/rhythmbox/plugins
      git clone git://github.com/aliva/rhythmbox-microblogger.git

    from Repositories
      Arch Linux                    : http://goo.gl/HwBvX (last version from git)
                                    : http://goo.gl/pA7aU (stable package)
      Frugalware Linux              : http://goo.gl/DFFu3

    from archive:
      tar -xvf rhythmbox-microblogger-[xxx].tar.gz
      mkdir -p ~/.gnome2/rhythmbox/plugins
      cp rhythmbox-microblogger ~/.gnome2/rhythmbox/plugins -Rf

  1- run/restart Rhythmbox active this plugin 'microblogger' and add accounts!

  2- now a button will appear in rhythmbox toolbar. use that for sending notice

  3- If you had problems. start rhythmbox with this command (debug mode)
        rhythmbox -D rhythmbox-microblogger
     and check output.

IMPORTANT
  * when I change the name of directory from 'rhythmbox-micoblogger' to something else
    plugin can not find images. so can not be activated.

  * You need these packages for this plugin (package names in Fedora)
    - Rhythmbox
    - python
    - gnome-python2-gconf
    - python-notify
    -- On other distros you may need python extra packages such as urllib, hashlib ....

